title: Jesse Cook - The Ultimate Jesse Cook
description:
[i]Never heard of these guy before. Give it a listen. Not into Latin or New Age or Flamenco? How about Latin New Age Flamenco!?! lol This is very lively music that still serves as nice background flavor. One thing is for certain is this is one of the best guitarist alive today.

And....you guessed it. MP3 tags have been edited so Disc 1 and Disc 2 show up under 1 Album in most players. 

- Big Papi[/i]


[quote]By H. L. Dietor on September

If you want music that will get you moving, yet be unabtrusive when necessary, this artist and his blend of flamenco meeting new age is for you. I've been listening to Cook for a few years now, having discovered him after my search for more music to expand my interest in acoustic guitar.

Following Leibert, Cook is one of my favorites. He truly knows his way around a guitar. And while I can't say I equally love every cut on this compilation, overall, I enjoy this set very much.

I know, I know, if you're a flamenco purist or snob, artists like him make you crazy and you'd never think to add him to your collection! But, for the rest of us who simply want something that makes us think, work by, relax by, entertain by, and makes you happy...well I don't think Cook can be beat. I'm hoping this really isn't The Ultimate Jesse Cook, because that would mean there's not much more to follow and I'm hoping for great new sounds from Cook for many listening years to come.[/quote]
